result.execSummary:
Charge(s) in this case were read in to this or other case(s). A "read in" charge is a charge that is dismissed as part of a plea agreement, however:

  • The defendant agrees to have the court consider the charge(s) when sentencing for another crime, under Wis. Stats. 973.20(1g)(b); and
  • The defendant cannot be prosecuted for these charge(s) in the future.

Notice to employers: It may be a violation of state law to discriminate against a job applicant because of an arrest or conviction record. Generally speaking, an employer may refuse to hire an applicant on the basis of a conviction only if the circumstances of the conviction substantially relate to the particular job. For more information, see Wisconsin Statute 111.335 and the Department of Workforce Development's publication, Arrest and Conviction Records under the Law.

records.addlTxt:
Defendant Tracie A Burg in court with attorney Anne Renc. Cass W Cousins appeared for the State of Wisconsin.
Cases heard are 15CM-156 and 15CT-14.

8:58 AM Court calls cases.
Atty Cousins states appearances.

Address is verified.

There is a plea agreement.

15CT-14: Defendant is pleading to Count 1. Count 2 would be dismissed. State makes recommendations: .197 test result, 22 days jail, $450 fine $1,505, $26.45, 15 mo IID, 15 mo revocation, DOT assessment. 15CM-156: Will be dismissed and read in but restitution of $188.32 to be ordered. Bond in this file is to cover the restitution and balance to be applied to 15CT-15.

Plea questionnaire/Agreement filed.

Court informs Defendant of charges and penalties.

Defendant enters a plea of: 
NO CONTEST Count 1, 15CT-14.

Court questions Defendant regarding plea.
Court informs Defendant of Constitutional Rights. Court advises Defendant of Elements State must prove for the Charge.
Court questions Attorney Renc for Defendant.
Court finds Defendant's Plea is freely, voluntarily and intelligently made.
Both attorneys stipulate that there is factual basis for the charge.

BY THE COURT:
Court finds a sufficient factual basis to support the charge.
Court finds the defendant guilty.  Clerk directed to enter Judgment of Conviction this date.
15CT-14 Count 1: OWI 2nd offense
15CT-14 Count 2: Dismissed
15CM-156: Dismissed and Read In

Atty Cousins makes sentencing arguments to the Court. 
Atty Renc makes sentencing arguments to the Court. 

Court believes the plea agreement is fair and appropriate.

BY THE COURT:
15CT-14:
Count 1:
Jail sentence for 22 Days
Huber granted for work, counseling and any other reason the Sheriff will allow
One half of jail sentence may be served on electronic monitor if Defendant qualifies
Report to jail today, sentence to commence within 60 days
Pay fine of $450 and costs totaling $1,505
Pay blood draw fee of $26.45
60 days to pay the fine and costs or set up payment plan
Drivers License Revoked for 15 Months
IID for 15 Months
DOT Assessment and Safety Plan  BAC: .197

15CM-156: (dismissed and read in case)
Pay Restitution of: $188.32 to Kevin Larson
Bond in this file is to be applied to restitution
Balance is to be applied to 15CT-14

Atty Renc has submitted an application for half priced iginition interlock device.
Court reviews application.
Court grants petition for half priced ignition interlock.
(already posted). Added:  No contact with Kevin Larson.  Allowed to go on time to the  residence with law enforcement to get personal belongings.
